Class PSItemChild

java.lang.Object
  com.percussion.cms.objectstore.PSDbComponent
      com.percussion.cms.objectstore.PSItemComponent
          com.percussion.cms.objectstore.PSItemChild
All Implemented Interfaces:
IPSCmsComponent, IPSDbComponent, Cloneable
public class PSItemChild
extends PSItemComponent

An object representation of the StandardItem.xsd Child element. Which is a Complex child, meaning it has 1 or more columns and 0 or more rows, which will be referred to in this class as 'childEntries'. In order for childEntries to be added to the child the childEntries are validated to ensure that they have the same field definitions, if they do they can be added to the Child. Therefore it is possible that childEntries, defined appropriately, may be shared across Child objects.

move

public void move(PSItemChildEntry childEntry,
                 int upDown)
If sequencing is enabled for this child, the order of the entries is preserved. childEntries are sequenced starting from 0 to n-1, where n is thenumber of entries contained by this child. 0 is considered the 'top' of the list. To move an item towards the top, supply a negative number.

Parameters:
childEntry - - the childEntry object to move.
upDown - -1 is up and 1 is down etc. The result of this + childEntryCount(), must be > 0 and < childEntryCount()

moveToPosition

public void moveToPosition(PSItemChildEntry childEntry,
                           int position)
Moves the supplied child entry from its current position to the specified position. isSequenced() must return true.

Parameters:
childEntry - The entry to move, must be found in the current list.
position - The new position, must be > 0 and < childEntryCount().

addEntry

public void addEntry(PSItemChildEntry childEntry)
Adds a PSItemChildEntry to the collection. The PSItemChildEntry must have valid PSItemField objects. That is one that was created by this object or one that has the same PSItemField as a PSItemChildEntry that is created by this object.

To ensure that the PSItemChildEntry is valid, use createChildEntry() to create the PSItemChildEntry.

Parameters:
childEntry - the object to add. Must not be null must have valid PSItemField objects.

equals

public boolean equals(Object obj)
Description copied from interface: IPSCmsComponent
Indicates whether some other object is "equal to" this one. All implementing classes must override this method as the default behavior is incorrect for deep clones. If the implementation does not follow the contract documented for this method in Object, then it must clearly state how it deviates from that contract. The following algorithm should be used:
  1. Call the base class (unless Object) and if true is returned, continue.
  2. Compare all members of current class.
  3. If all members are equal, return true.
